      public static CallSite duckTypeCall(MethodHandles.Lookup lk, String name, MethodType type)
      A call site that implements duck-typing calls for a given method and signature. The receiver object that would be this is passed as first argument to the call site target. Up to 8 class types are cached for fast invocation.
      Parameters:
      lk - caller lookup
      name - caller name
      type - caller type
      Returns:
      a DuckTypeCallSite

    • duckTypeCall

      public static CallSite duckTypeCall(MethodHandles.Lookup lk, String name, MethodType type, int polymorphism)
      A call site that implements duck-typing calls for a given method and signature. The receiver object that would be this is passed as first argument to the call site target. The number of class types cached for fast invocation is configurable.
      Parameters:
      lk - caller lookup
      name - caller name
      type - caller type
      polymorphism - amount of calling types to cache handles for
      Returns:
      a DuckTypeCallSite

    • lookupAndInvoke

      public static CallSite lookupAndInvoke(MethodHandles.Lookup lk, String callerName, MethodType callerType, MethodHandle lookupHandle)
      A constant call site that when its target is invoked, will call lookupHandle with the caller's lookup, name, method type, and the arguments for that invocation to lookup the target method handle to be called for that invocation as if by invoke. lookupHandle must accept a subset of arguments compatible with the caller type (as in MethodHandles.foldArguments) and return a method handle with the same type as the caller type.
      No target caching of any kind is performed. If the call site will be invoked repeatedly, consider writing a custom call site instead.
      Parameters:
      lk - caller lookup
      callerName - caller name
      callerType - caller type
      lookupHandle - the method handle that will be called to lookup the target method handle to invoke.
      Returns:
      a ConstantCallSite

    • lookupAndInvokeExact

      public static CallSite lookupAndInvokeExact(MethodHandles.Lookup lk, String callerName, MethodType callerType, MethodHandle lookupHandle)
      A constant call site that when its target is invoked, will call lookupHandle with the caller's lookup, name, method type, and the arguments for that invocation to lookup the target method handle to be called for that invocation as if by invokeExact. lookupHandle must accept a subset of arguments compatible with the caller type (as in MethodHandles.foldArguments) and return a method handle with the same type as the caller type.
      No target caching of any kind is performed. If the call site will be invoked repeatedly, consider writing a custom call site instead.
      Parameters:
      lk - caller lookup
      callerName - caller name
      callerType - caller type
      lookupHandle - the method handle that will be called to lookup the target method handle to invoke.

      a ConstantCallSite
